ective by comparing the approach in these kindred legal systems, providing a benchmark for both.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCivil lawxScotland. 0aCivil lawxSouth Africa. 0aCivil lawzScotlandvCongresses. 0aCivil lawzScotland. 0aCivil lawzSouth AfricavCongresses. 0aCivil lawzSouth Africa. 0aHuman rightsxScotland. 0aHuman rightsxSouth Africa. 0aHuman rightszScotlandvCongresses. 0aHuman rightszScotland. 0aHuman rightszSouth AfricavCongresses. 0aHuman rightszSouth Africa. 4aLaw. 7aLAW / Civil Law.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Ross Gilbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnard-Naudé, Jaco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlackie, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBois, François du, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchell, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabrelli, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFagan, Anton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeris, Loretta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaing, Sheldon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoubser, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, David Carey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilo, J. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMostert, Hanri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaisley, Roderick R. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPretoriu